The paper deals with the problem of deploying sensors using a drone, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves optimization and decision-making, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves submodular optimization, which is a well-studied topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a drone for sensor deployment involves control and coordination, which are topics in systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of simulations and physical experiments, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV).
